to confirm

28:56.169 --> 28:58.649
that it was Mack who used it,
I called his fiancé,

28:58.693 --> 29:00.564
who insisted
they were on a trip

29:00.608 --> 29:01.957
the day Mark was killed.

29:02.001 --> 29:03.045
Cristal, that can't be true.

29:03.089 --> 29:05.178
We know that he
was here that day.

29:05.221 --> 29:07.180
I called him here.

29:07.223 --> 29:09.530
Alexis told me she saw him.And you believe her?

29:09.573 --> 29:10.966
Well, she would have
no reason to lie.

29:11.010 --> 29:13.229
When did she ever need a reason?

29:13.273 --> 29:14.796
Well, you can
go ask her yourself.

29:14.840 --> 29:16.493
I'm sure she's
camped out at the bar.

29:16.537 --> 29:18.321
She's here?

29:18.365 --> 29:22.673
Yeah, she told me
that you invited her.

29:22.717 --> 29:23.892
That you two had called a truce.

29:23.936 --> 29:25.372
Oh, did she?

29:25.415 --> 29:29.593
Well, the truce is about
to be called off in a big way.

29:41.170 --> 29:42.476
Seriously?
I don't need an encore,

29:42.519 --> 29:44.478
and I already told you
I'm not leaving.

29:44.521 --> 29:47.524
I'm not here to convince you
to leave, I promise.

29:47.568 --> 29:49.222
I am actually here to apologize.

29:49.265 --> 29:52.660
I know that I can be
a bit pushy.

29:52.703 --> 29:55.837
I think you mean a lot pushy,
like aggressively so.

29:55.881 --> 30:00.189
Okay, fine, but I swear
I really just came here to help.

30:00.233 --> 30:02.670
I just forgot to listen
to what you wanted,

30:02.713 --> 30:03.932
and though everyone else
is right

30:03.976 --> 30:05.455
for wanting you to come back,

30:05.499 --> 30:08.850
that doesn't mean you're wrong
for wanting to stay, Kirby.

30:08.894 --> 30:11.331
I want you to be able
to make your own decisions.

30:11.374 --> 30:14.769
And if your next decision
is going to Sri Lanka,

30:14.813 --> 30:16.684
then at least

30:16.727 --> 30:20.557
I was here to say
I'm sorry and goodbye.

30:30.263 --> 30:32.178
All right, everyone,
and before we leave,

30:32.221 --> 30:34.833
let's get down to business
and talk naming rights.

30:34.876 --> 30:37.183
And I think it's time
we honor today's win.

30:37.226 --> 30:39.620
How about a shot for every goal
the Atlantix scored?

30:42.449 --> 30:43.711
MICHAEL:
Oh, come on.

30:43.754 --> 30:45.931
Where's that enthusiasm?

30:45.974 --> 30:47.628
You didn't
just come here

30:47.671 --> 30:49.804
for a free ride on a plane,
did you?

30:51.632 --> 30:53.547
I know I speak
for everyone when I say

30:53.590 --> 30:55.810
we appreciate the hospitality,

30:55.854 --> 30:58.291
but our involvement was
a show of respect to Jeff.

30:58.334 --> 30:59.770
MICHAEL:
Well, if you really

30:59.814 --> 31:01.903
respected Jeff, you would've
voiced your concerns

31:01.947 --> 31:04.863
before you wasted
this club's time and money.

31:06.342 --> 31:08.954
Since that ship has sailed,
what do you want from us now?

31:08.997 --> 31:11.608
Honest conversation.

31:11.652 --> 31:13.654
Well, no one here,
except maybe the hotel guy,

31:13.697 --> 31:15.177
is going to drop
hundreds of millions

31:15.221 --> 31:17.788
of dollars for the right to put
their logo on a stadium

31:17.832 --> 31:20.095
when it's advertising
no one may ever see.

31:20.139 --> 31:22.445
BOB:
Let's be honest,
your stadium is in the center

31:22.489 --> 31:23.925
of a crap neighborhood,

31:23.969 --> 31:26.928
and if your team folds,
we wouldn't even be able

31:26.972 --> 31:28.930
to repurpose the stadium
for anything worthwhile.

31:30.671 --> 31:33.195
Where you see
a crap neighborhood,

31:33.239 --> 31:36.024
I see a community
that transcends this sport.

31:36.068 --> 31:38.113
If we asked our fans

31:38.157 --> 31:40.594
to donate their money to put
their name on our stadium,

31:40.637 --> 31:42.726
we'd reach our goal
in five minutes.

31:42.770 --> 31:45.120
Because unlike you,
they're real people

31:45.164 --> 31:47.209
that have come together
to support a community

31:47.253 --> 31:50.996
in a city overlooked
by greedy corporate bosses.

31:53.085 --> 31:55.217
Now get off our damn plane.

31:57.002 --> 31:58.220
ADAM:
So you failed.

31:58.264 --> 32:00.135
No, no.
The mission changed.

32:00.179 --> 32:02.355
So, technically
it was a success.

32:02.398 --> 32:04.748
I'm not sure Anders would
agree that his daughter

32:04.792 --> 32:07.186
going off to Sri Lanka with
some fake guru is a success.

32:07.229 --> 32:08.622
Why do you care?

32:08.665 --> 32:10.972
You only agreed to help
so that you could get back in

32:11.016 --> 32:12.626
with the devil
known as Dad.

32:12.669 --> 32:15.368
Hey, I think you'd feel
differently about things

32:15.411 --> 32:16.891
if you knew the truth.

32:16.935 --> 32:19.676
Okay, well, I mean, we've got
about a week of walking left

32:19.720 --> 32:21.504
until we hit civilization,
so please enlighten me

32:21.548 --> 32:23.245
on our murderous father.

32:25.204 --> 32:26.509
All right. Okay.

32:26.553 --> 32:28.337
Blake did what he did

32:28.381 --> 32:31.993
only after he found out that
Mack shot Mark Jennings.

32:32.037 --> 32:35.170
And that gunshot spooked
Cristal's horse,

32:35.214 --> 32:37.694
